32 SECTION 18. (1) Not later than the date on which the report of the highway cost allo-
33 cation study is due under ORS 366.506 (5), the Department of Transportation shall submit a
34 report, in the manner provided in ORS 192.245, to the interim committees of the Legislative
35 Assembly related to revenue and transportation, that recommends a rate for the per-mile
36 road usage charge that would sustainably raise the revenue necessary to maintain the public
37 highways of this state.
38 (2) The report must include:
39 (a) The total estimated cost for maintenance and preservation of Oregon’s transportation
40 system, including for local systems; and
41 (b) An estimate of the total vehicle miles driven on the public highways of this state
42 based on the most recently available data on vehicle miles traveled.
43 (3) For purposes of subsection (2)(a) of this section, the department shall establish met-
44 rics by which maintenance and preservation needs are evaluated and reported, including but
45 not limited to:
